modules.description: This module provides functions for generating cryptographically secure random data. It operates on a generator state type `g` and supports generating random bytes either into a new string or directly into an existing bytes buffer. Concrete use cases include creating random session keys, nonces, or initialization vectors for cryptographic protocols.

This module provides cryptographically secure random number generation for MirageOS, supporting operations to seed generators and produce random bytes, integers, and identifiers. It centers around the generator state type `g`, allowing both fresh and in-place generation of random data in strings or bytes buffers. Submodules extend this functionality to specialized use cases like generating session keys, nonces, and initialization vectors. Example uses include creating secure tokens for authentication or random identifiers in networked applications.
